32:
"Stars shall sing... for ye who hold this 
ring..."
47:
I knew it! That glow was from the 
World Flipper!
50:
Whoa... This thing's CRAZY! No wonder 
you guys are known as Godkings!
55:
It's pretty damn good proof of who 
I am.
59:
Yeah.
So... mind helping a bro out, one last 
time?
61:
Sure. Just tell me what you need me 
to do!
64:
Same as last time. Shut up, look pretty, 
and leave all the talking to me!
67:
Hah. Watch it, smartass. You're talkin' to 
a prince.
71:
YOU watch it, or I'll start using biiig 
fancy court words.
75:
...The Godking Selenius Whitetail wishes 
for peace. Chief, will you sign the 
treaty?
78:
A ring is no proof of royalty. 
You must've scavenged it from the 
graveyard.
81:
Even after all this, you still won't cooperate...
Fine. You leave me no choice.
82:
You are now dismissed from your role 
as chief of the catfolk.
91:
Even have it in writing! The one on the 
left's your notice of dismissal, and the 
one on the right's proof of MY 
appointment!
93:
All the clans have signed them! 
The bombays, angoras, tabbies, 
calicos, panthers, and even the tigers!
98: Is this your idea of a joke?!
100:
What of the pain we endured?! 
The indignities?!
104:
Those are YOUR grudges, not ours! 
We shouldn't have to fight a war for 
them!
107:
Please, Grampa. Please.
I don't know what else to tell you.
111: No one wants to fight but you.
113:
You carried this village through some 
rough times, but it's over now. You've 
done enough.
115:
It's about time you got some rest. 
Right... "Gramp-gramp"?
126:
Everything'll be fine, Grampa! Just kick 
back, relaaax, and leave the rest to me!
137:
What was that, Light?
You glowed for a second there.
141:
It was faint, but I felt some of my old 
power.
144:
You and Stella's starchart HAVE to share 
some kind of connection then.
So... did you find Light's world, Stella?
148: No. Light's world is not in this region.
151:
*sigh* Well, guess that would've been 
TOO easy…
156:
Hey, there's no rush.
This is what we want anyways, right? 
Fill in the starchart, get Light up and 
running again.
160: Yeah! Slow and steady wins the race!
166:
Claw, Albert... What are you two doing 
here?
170:
Just swinging by to see you off.
Man, I can't BELIEVE you were telling 
the truth about there being other 
worlds and stuff. That was AWESOME!
173:
I trust you weren't thinking of slipping 
off before we got a chance to thank 
you properly.
178:
Nimbus rushed us over. You know how 
bashful he gets.
182:
Can it. I thought we should hurry, 
that's all.
186:
Bro... You're not gonna stay in the 
canyon?
189: Nah. I'm not cut out to be a king.
191:
Sides, I'd just get in your way. Right, 
"Chief"?
198:
Regardless of where your journey takes 
you, we'll never forget the great service 
you've done these lands.
200:
You have our deepest gratitude, and 
I vow we shall one day repay the debt 
in kind!
203:
Yeah! I'm really glad I got to meet you, 
bro!
205:
And I'm not just buttering you up. 
I mean it!
211:
It's gonna be weird havin' some peace 
and quiet again.
216: That is no way to talk to friends.
218:
...There is no debt between us.
Without your aid, we would never have 
found the World Flipper... and Nimbus 
would not have learned who he truly is.
221: Thank you for taking care of us.
224:
I hope the truce goes well.
We're all rooting for you!
228:
Heh. I'm sure everything'll be fine with 
them in charge.
